<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 27 at 5:07PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A Band of Snow and Gusty Winds to bring difficult travel
conditions...
A band of snow has developed over Fergus county. Snow associated
with this band may reduce visibility to a half mile or less.
Heavy snow, in combination with gusty winds will make travel
difficult. If you are able to, delay travel for a couple hours to
allow the band of snow to pass southward. Overall, expect snow to
last in any specific location around an hour or less.</description>
